1. INTRODUCTION

 This program generates MIDI Note Numbers. It can be
 used as a MIDI Keyboard to control any MIDI device
 (a synthesizer, a sound module...)

 It works on Workbench v3.0 or higher, and hasn't been
 tested on earlier versions.

 You must have MUI installed... and have a Midi Interface.

 This program uses the midi.library (see @{"Installation" Link "INSTALLATION"})

 I put the source in it because you may not have
 a "azerty" or "qwerty" keyboard, so you could
 change it.

@EndNode

@Node "INSTALLATION" "NotoOn.guide/INSTALLATION"
@Next "BUTTONS"
@Prev "INTRODUCTION"
@Toc "Main"

2. INSTALLATION

 The only thing you have to do is to copy the file "libs/midi.library"
 in you LIBS: directory.

@EndNode

@Node "BUTTONS" "NoteOn_English.guide/BUTTONS"
@Next "REGISTRATION"
@Prev "INSTALLATION"
@Toc "Main"

3. BUTTONS

 What are all those buttons for ?


 The 4 first lines are the keyboard itself.
 As you push the button (or its shortcut) the program
 generates a Midi Note On signal on the specified
 MidiChannel, at the specified Velocity for the right
 Note Number.

 The MidiChannel slider changes the basic Midi Channel.

 The Velocity slider changes the default velocity, which
 will be used for every note sent. (ah, if a computer
 keyboard had velocity control !...)

 To quit, just close the window...

@EndNode

